Manifest - shows which version/commit of each module was used
Build configuration - shows output of the configure summary for the app (possibly formatted nicely)
Log - shows the last 20/30 lines of the log, along with a button to download the full thing

How to organise this page if many apps/branches? Particular issue if part of an organization - might have access to many apps, but only work on a subset of them. Focus/interest in particular apps will change over tim.

Apps can be owned by organizations or individuals, but not teams.

What does being an app owner practically mean? How is it functionally different from being an administrator? Maybe we don't need the concept of an owner, or a "transfer ownership" action (transfering ownership would simply be a matter of adding a new admin and removing your membership).

It has been speculated that we'll need a way to identify an application in Flathub as belonging to the application's official author(s). While this make well play a role in publishing an app on the store, it isn't clear what role it would play in Flathub itself.
